caption: Everything we tried was amazing, and our waiter was great! Great location, great atmosphere, great food, don't sleep on this place!
Great ambience. Great food. Chicken tikka masala and lamb vindaloo was on point. Cocktails are good too.

We are so thankful that Pappe has made it through the past year. Not all great restaurants have and that is extremely sad. Pappe delivers on-point dishes with a true, authentic touch of goodness. Ask for it spicy, and you get it spicy! 5 solid stars!
I love the food! It’s a tad pricey, but it’s not crazy by DC standards. My favorite are the samosas or crab pav. Definitely worth a visit if you like Indian food.

I arrive at this unique restaurant from time to time since I love the good mood that is outline this restaurant. The crew is highly attentive and skilfull. The service is exceptionally efficient. Needless to say, the food they serve is good. I visited many times and I was always joyful. The cost is honest. I recommend this restaurant to to all.

We tried two other high-rated Indian restaurants before Pappe but they were disappointments. Pappe exceeded our expectations with the quality and taste. We ordered, among other things, Kaju Mutter Paneer and Missi Roti. Excellent taste. Their Aloo-Gobhi is out of this world. Roti is as close as you can get to a home-made one and has amazing taste. Only disappointment is the small quantity served and the mango lassi (that was not fresh and poured in our glasses straight from the freezer).
This place was a fantastic find when I was visiting DC for work. Fantastic food and drinks too.
Samosa Chaat was amazing - best I have ever had. Did not get to try any other dishes

some of the best Indian Food I have had in quite some time. I had just looked this place up on Google maps and I am so happy I did. The was perfect (servers name: Michael R.) and the food was phenomenal. I had gotten the Goan Smoke which is a Inadn inspired mezcal drink and I liked it so much I had to get another. and the mushroom truffle nan was outstanding. I will surely come here every time in Im town.

Ordered tonight on Caviar and after an entire hour of waiting with a confirmed order the restaurant cancelled my order because they were too busy. The delivery person was waiting for our food to pick it up.

We ordered tonight through Caviar and the restaurant canceled the order ONE HOUR after we submitted it. The app said the delivery person was there waiting and then suddenly it gets canceled. Caviar said it was because they were too busy. A full hour later. What a joke.

Great flavorful dishes. The lamb item that I ordered was a good cut of meat. I enjoyed the food here and will go back. The ambiance is nice, but could be better. I would give the food itself 4.5 out of 5.
We had a wonderful  at this restaurant. We enjoyed the extraordinary vibes and the menu. The waiters were super friendly. I’m content we finally decided to eat here.
I had a poor rearmament and bad food.

Ambience is good, but the food is not good. I ordered bengan Bartha and this was the first time I had it without seeing the Bengan visible and it looks mashed which is not a good thing and the roti that came with it was small and they are charging around 6$ for service tax and the waiter is rude asking if I have been to that restaurant before, when I asked a question

I have not had a drink mixed as well as Michael mixed mine in a long time. Since moving to the DMV, nobody has surpassed him. More than worth the five stars, I recommend seeing if Michael is available if you come in.

Nice and cozy atmosphere with fantastic food made by chef Sanjay. Enjoyed lamb kabob, veg.samosas and crab cake mini burger. Great customer service provided by attentive staff. Outside seating is available now! Cheers to the weekend.
One of the best restaurants in DC!

We enjoy going out. Last night we arrived in this excellent place which we didn’t know before. We passed a beautiful experience there with delicious food and a courteous crew and a great  chef. We  added this fine restaurant in our list  and we shall surely go again soon.  Highly recommended.

Soooo delicious! Their curbside is very easy and efficient. They forgot my chicken so I called back and they worked with me. Flavors are just so good! Great food and great costumer service. Will definitely go back.

This is by far my favorite Indian restaurant since coming to DC. I have never had a bad experience with food at the restaurant (have had take out numerous times). I will say the food is on the spicier side, which I love but isn't for everyone.

O M G the best Indian in DC. My husband and I are from Ireland and England, having lived in London for years prior to moving to DC so we love a good curry. We’ve tried a few places in DC, eventually eating in Pappe on restaurant week in the winter. We had an amaaaaazing meal with great service then and tried them again this week during quarantine. It was the best meal we’ve had since the start of lockdown and we’ve been ordering in a lot. The saag paneer is great, the raita was delicious, the samosa papdi chaat was class. We also got onion bhajia; we thought we’d never find them in the US after a few failed attempts elsewhere so it was sooo good to find them here, definitely order those.  I will struggle not to order from here every weekend!
Amazing food and great service, will definitely come back!
Good food, but we went on a busy night perhaps, wait was long for the dishes to get to the table

I had a vegeterain deluxe thali..and my husband and cousin shared a lamb briyani and goat curry. They were very happy with the dishes.. honestly I din like my thali much..curies were very bland , palak paneer gravy was spectacular. Ambience , and service is great.
Awesome Indian food and great service
This place is delicious.  I came solo as none of my colleagues wanted Indian food.  So glad I did, it's some of the best I've had
My first time here..  I ordered the t taar gosht and it was really delicious.

My first time here..  I ordered the t taar gosht and it was really delicious. The customer service was superb. I was seated as soon as I walked into the restaurant. The place is very ambiance but the seating is kind of Built-in a little tight. All in all I love the food that I received. the lamb was really tender.  my friend ordered the lamb leg and she said it was really delicious. the butter naan went well with both our meals.
Awesome vibe, good food, excellent service!

Went here for dinner with a friend — definitely hit the spot with the right ambience, great service, and tasty food. Unsurprisingly, it was a little more expensive than I think it deserves. For instance, naan is extra and you need to pay $3-4 for ONE piece of naan (vs paying for a few pieces); feels as if the restaurant is taking advantage of the 14th area and clientele. We ordered tiki masala, lamb biryani, palak paneer (side order size), and naan and all were tasty and definitely enough food. I would definitely come back but would be mindful of what i am ordering if anyone is on a budget!

I love DC. Truly, I do. I lived here for a long time, then moved away, but I was able to return this week for a visit to friends and family while touring some new spots that have popped up since I've been gone. Pappe is one of those spots and WOW am I glad we made time for it. I'll start with atmosphere - hip, laid-back, and clean with tasteful decor that is at once theme-appropriate without falling into appropriation. Staff is attentive, fast, and friendly even with relatively large groups. Whatever happens, do NOT miss out on the naan bread - there are several varieties, so make sure to get a basket so you can try them all! Garlic is my favorite, but the butter version is very helpful for highlighting the amazing sauces and curries without detracting too much from the flavor. It comes with a sort of green cilantro/mint chutney which is delightful in its own right and certainly has a little bit of "attitude" if you put too much on your bread. We ended up ordering the chicken tikka masala (of course, since it's literally everyone's favorite), the fiery chicken vindaloo, the aloo tikka chaat, and the shrimp malabar. I'll start with the aloo tikka chaat which was refreshing and had a very fun flavor profile, not unlike a divine love child of ceviche, hummus, and samosas (but with a completely unique approach). I expected it to come as a sort of sauce to put on potato pancakes, but it's actually more like a bowl you serve yourself out of and eat with the potato pancakes already at the bottom. Definitely a winner. Of the three entrees, the chicken tikka masala was exactly what you expect it to be - tried and true and easy for folks who are relatively new to Indian food (we aren't - we just love that dish). The shrimp malabar was my unexpected favorite - creamy, generous, and full of complimentary flavors that brought out the best in everything around it. However, I want to go on record and tell everyone to #respectthevindaloo because I certainly did not at first so I was face-first in the basmati rice and water glasses for a minute afterward! I am usually one that is very welcoming and adventurous with spicy food, but this one caught me off-guard. We ordered it with chicken only because one of our party did not eat lamb, but I expect the lamb would have been even better than the chicken. However, be warned that it is definitely a dish that is aptly named and not among the merciful dishes for folks who are sensitive to spices. However, it is absolutely delicious! Enjoy and be sure to share!
Worst service and fake Indian food
Worst service!
Pretty good food and great service.
Amazing taste. Dessert is fine, curry is spicy.
Amazing service and cocktails!

Food was fine, but happy hour pricing was a bait and switch. The bar menu says "$4 drafts" but apparently it only applies to one of the five drafts, which they do not tell you. The bill arrived with my two draft beers at $8 each, which is when the bartender told me. I wasn't prepared to argue in the middle of a busy restaurant.

A very posh India restaurant. Indian restaurant but mostly operates on American labor. Tastes of not all the items we ordered were great, but a few of them were good, a few were sub-par. Overall a mixed bag. A little bit on the pricier side also. Mostly paid street parking is available outside.
Good food decent service. Interesting looking bar. Small place tho with decor that looks both contemporary but dinggy.

Went alone while on a 2 day trip to DC. Sat at the bar ant had the best of time! I let the barmen pick many items on the menu to discover and everyting was super delicious. Try the Gobi Manchurian with the cardamom Gimlet (a drink)! The guys were superfriendly almost like friends. Thanks guys!
Overrated. Not much of good quality just fancy

Great ambience. Amazing food. The waiters and the hostess were super courteous and friendly. The prices are reasonable and they offer half portions if you just want to try a bunch of dishes. Had Malai Kofta and Aloo Tikki Chat and both were delicious!!

I can not comment on the food because we didn't stay long enough to eat. Our group of six sat at the first booth on the left. I sat next to the wall and the pipe's condensation above kept dripping down on my head and on the table where my plate would have been. It also was dripping on the person across from me who was also sitting beside the wall. The staff said it was the condensation and there was nothing they could do.They were not able to reseat us for an hour, so we left.

Worst experience ever I had in dc. The servicing was pathetic. Even though the restaurant did not seem to be crowded but we were still made to wait for around 40 min and than the guy was even not sorry and was telling us that he took only 5 min and that we are lying. I understand that it might take time to take the order some time but the behavior of the guy was so un welcoming. I wish I could leave the negative ratings.

Was one of my favorites but the last couple of visits have been disappointing with some items being taken off the menu, some items not being close to the earlier taste, the size of the servings being reduced.  The place looks upscale and still deserves a visit for the ambience.
The food was amazing! Toby was our server when we sat at the bar because we came at four for happy hour which has half priced apps! The apps are INCREDIBLE and the drinks great! Will be back!

I came for lunch with my office a few months ago and we all loved our dishes. I got the vegetarian thali, which for me was a nice way to try some additional dishes I was not as familiar with, without taking a big risk. My favorite was the daal fry. I recently went to make a reservation for lunch and was sad to discover that lunch is not available during the week, but it is good to know delivery is now an option.
Nice, but the food was kind of bland

I go to many Indian restaurants in an area of NJ with a very large Indian population. The dishes in the NJ indian restaurants seems much tastier than those serverd at Pappe. In addition, they wouldn't serve roti with onion or garlic, something that always seems to be done if asked in the NJ restaurants. We chose this restaurant only because it was very close to where I was staying, and did have vegetarian dishes. For that reason, it seemed to be a good choice, but I wouldn't drive out of the way to go there.
My favorite restaurant in the city! Try the malabar curry

Went for dinner here tonight, solo on a work trip, sitting at the bar. The bartender was awesome! Very nice, attentive and helpful. Great conversation — so I highly recommend for other road warriors who find themselves eating solo.  I had the Butter Chicken and the Garlic Naan. Both were overwhelming amazing, but I had to dock a star for two very basic things that were easily avoidable and brought the overall quality of the experience down.  First, the rice was dry. It was very unfortunate because it was very fragrant and otherwise good tasting, but dry rice just kind of ruins everything. Second, I found two small bones in the Butter Chicken. Not the end of the world, but they were of a concerning size because they could be a choking hazard.

Authentic North Indian cuisine and good service. I have been here multiple times for lunch, drinks and dinner. Every visit has been excellent. The ingredients and spices taste high-quality and rich. Indian food is a personal favorite type of cuisine and this restaurant ranks among the best I've had in 20 years of West and East coast living.
Nice place but the food is little blended
Okay food for indian spice heat score the food is bland

This is my new favorite indian restaurant to order delivery from. There's a few decent Indian restaurants in DC. Indigo for more of a budget option and Rasika and Bombay Club. Compared to Rasika and Bombay Club. Those places are good but most of the dishes tend to be a little too rich for me.

I love the food they serve here - it’s flavorful and delicious and I used to recommend everyone to come here because I love the food so much. But a recent dining experience will never make me go back again.  I left my phone in the restaurant and realized as soon as I got home, roughly 10 minutes after as my friend had driven me back. Once I realized, I was able to contact my boyfriend to have him call the restaurant. I used my Find My iPhone which located the phone at Pappe. He called twice, and in those calls, the restaurant claimed that they had not seen a phone, that there were two people dining where I was sitting, and that they would “check later.”  Instead of waiting, I simply went back to the restaurant. 40 minutes had elapsed since I was last there. No one was currently sitting where I had been sitting, and in 40 minutes, were they really able to clear the table, seat another set of guests (it wasn’t busy on a Tuesday evening), and clear their plates as well and swap with new plates and silverware? Then, it took me demanding to see a manager for someone to give me back my phone - I don’t know why it took 2 phone calls and an in person visit to actually “find it,” when it should have been found immediately because it was left on the seat. This is super shady behavior by the employees here and is so disappointing to see in an established business - a place you think would have a lot more integrity and a lot more care for its customers.  Food is great, but be wary of the service. Looks like from other reviews that other shady behavior has been going on at Pappe.

We went on a sat evening without a reservation and the lady in the front said it’s an hour of wait time. We have our names and went out but she called us in 15 minutes saying our table is ready.  She was not very polite to us.  Coming to the food, we ordered 4 items out of which two are ok and two are very good so it’s a mixed feeling. Samosa-2.5/5, they were very oily Aloo Pandi chat-2/5, it doesn’t have the tang flavor in it. Chilli Naan- This is excellent, if you are going here this is a must. Be careful it is spicy. Korma-The flavor and the taste was really good. Finally they had a good bar collection.
Great food and ambiance.

While the food here is quite good (though needed a touch of salt, and more importantly for the paneer tikka, needed to be warm...), the service was not great. The person who greeted us was rude and unwelcoming, and instead of walking us to our table, pointed to it several times to indicate we should walk over ourselves. It felt like we were intruding and this already put a bad taste in our mouths (we had a reservation!). Then, it took an extremely long time for any server to take interest in us. In fact we were seconds from just getting up and leaving when someone finally stopped by. Disappointing! I won't be coming back - especially because the food is on the pricier side, so one would expect service to match.

I had the vegetarian thali and it was a wonderful lunch! I was disappointed to hear they won't be serving lunch anymore, but would definitely recommend going for dinner and trying everything possible. Everything I tried did a great job of balancing flavor and heat, and I liked the touch of complimentary unlimited masala chai. The place is beautifully decorated and I was happy to see it so crowded on a Friday afternoon for lunch. Pappe makes a great addition to the 14th St family and I'm glad to have such good Indian so nearby.

Very dishonest enterprise. The waitress gave herself an extra (undeserved) tip on top of the one I put on the receipt. I did not discover this until I received the credit card statement some weeks later and had to resolve the overpay through Visa. The restaurant never apologized or acknowledged the problem. If you go to Pappe - and there are many better choices for Indian food in NW DC - you should be aware of this and make sure you check your credit card statement to see if they've inflated the amount you authorize as a tip.

Didn't have a reservation, waited only a couple minutes to be seated on a Friday night (it was busy). Place is nice enough, exposed brick and industrial style with ornamental pillows/curtains/and what looks like saris overhanging tables. Out of place looking bar right in the middle of the restaurant. Service was ok. Thought we were getting a free starter - turns out they just delivered it to the wrong table. Didn't see a waiter after being seated for a fairly long time (15+ minutes). Waiter forgot our drink order - have us a free drink too compensate. Not terrible, but not amazing. Food was hit or miss - yogurt explosions were fantastic, samosas were dinky/wimpy for what you're paying, and the portion sizes run a little smaller than I was hoping for the entrees. Pros were that the mushroom truffle naan was the star of the show, so good. Chicken in the chicken Tikka Masala was perfectly cooked and the curry was great - strong, savory, spicy; there just wasn't enough of it to warrant $17. Other entree we tried was aloo gobi (potato's and cauliflower) - not good, weak flavor for the cauliflower, seemed as if they were tossed into the small amount of curry at the end. Rice was dry. Presentation wasn't anything spectacular (except the yogurt explosion - those looked great). Overall, middle of the road food experience. Tldr: If you're going to go here, start with the yogurt explosion, get the mushroom truffle naan, and have the chicken Tikka Masala. Forgive the rice, and steer clear of samosas and aloo gobi.

Lousy service. The food is good but they took a really long time to even come and take our order. We reached there around 7.45pm and they got our appetizers almost around 8.45pm. It took even longer for the entree’s. The person taking our orders was very rude and arrogant.  I would prefer ordering the food or pickup but will not recommend dine in.
Excellent Indian for DC. Proper vindaloo. The truffle naan is a must!  Very good service. Try to get seated at one of their cozy booths. Reservations are recommended.
Good and nice place to have indian food. Quick service.
This is the place that should not be missed if you are in DC and a fan of Indian food.  Every single entree  ordered was amazing 5 star ratings from front desk to waiters to chef. 👍
Always the best Indian in the city Sanjay is the #KingOfVindaloo
Great food. Vindaloo sauce is spicy with the right amount of flavor
Very authentic and professional high quality restaurant Highly recommended !!

Food was good, naan , specially the truffle naan were great, we had goat, lamb, spinach kofta, bhindi and gulab jamun for dessert,  service was fantastic,  Brand was specially nice and took care of our every little need. Cardamom gin was delicious.  When you have so many choices in DC I think finding this gem was a lucky thing. I will be back and highly recommend others to go here at least once.
Excellent whiskey cocktail, and the lamb pollack was cooked perfectly, one of the best Indian dishes I've ever had. It was a little oversalted, but I couldn't bring myself to give 4-stars for that.
Great food, good service, decent prices.

Great Curry, Butter Chicken und Chicken Tikka Masala! Atmosphere and Ambiance is traditional, neat and comfortable. The restaurant appears super clean. Servers are pleasant and communicative. And most importantly the food is nicely presented, taste was delicious to a good price point. I can highly recommend the Chicken Tikka Masala!
Absolutely incredible. Great cocktails,  happy hour special, curry choices (vegetarian, vegan and meat lovers). Have the chicken palak curry, itll blow your mind.  And the rosemary naan. :)
Mango lassi - sour. Chicken Tikka - burnt. Seekh Kebab -burnt. Worst dinner ever.

My friend and I went there for their soft opening due by coincidence. It was my first time trying Indian cuisine, and I was completely blown away. It was fairly priced, incredible food, and great service. The butter chicken and garlic naan were unbeatable, I can't wait to come back!

Great food in with authentic style and flavors. You can tell time is put into preparing dishes in an authentic way. Tender and delicious nail gosht and great butter chicken. Great tandoori breads. Cocktails could be more imaginative. Setting is warm and inviting. Staff is attentive.

Appetiser was very good specially vegetarian... but main course is ok ok ... if u looking Indian taste then don’t go this place ... if u are non-vegetarian then must try laal Maas... also food is expensive and service is very poor .. wait time was a long ... if u go there confirm your reservation..

Loved the texture, quality and ambience. A perfect place for non-indians to try authentic Indian cuisine. Mild to lightly spiced variety and amazing choice of breads. Both, whole wheat roti and mint lachcha paratha were the best I have had in the US. Good going Pappe!
We had a huge party but our cool waitress was able to accommodate us. Kept the drinks coming, and the food was delicious. Highly recommended and $$ friendly.

So good, the vindaloo will burn your face off but you'll love every minute of it.  Great atmosphere and friendly and knowledgeable service, they will order for you if you want and you won't regret any of it.
attended a friend's birthday and so delighted to enjoy this yummy food
friendly service & yummy curry !!! LOVE this place!!!
Not worth for money. No taste in food. Though it has Vegetarian dishes but not like typical Indian Food.
Good service, great food and terrific ambience
Very good Indian restaurant with traditional food
The Indian taste that Pappe offers in a friendly environment with Indian music and Indian decor is definitely praiseworthy.
Do yourself a favor and stop in here.
Tasty Indian food and great service..
5/5 great food
Amazingly delicious and well executed food!
It’s been a while since I had decent Indian meal in a restaurant setting. Pappe left a lingering delightful taste of home in my mouth . Majority of food items we ordered were delicious.
Excellent butter chicken.
Really nice boho vibe to the place. Great apps and cocktails

I went in as they opened. The place was empty. I waited at the hosts desk as he talked on the phone. He never acknowledged me. Some other fellow came up and asked me to wait. Eventually I gave up and walked up.
Too expensive and food taste is normal
Terrible service ! We waited for our Drinks which never came. Our waitee was rude!
The food is good, but there's one extremely rude manager. 1 star in order to get your attention.
Awesome food, great service!!

This is by far the best restaurant offering north Indian cuisine in DC area.  The curry flavors were authentic and amazing. The Quantity of food is good. The chat appetizers were sweet and tangy as well. Will definitely visit this place again. The staff was friendly and ambience was cozy. I would reccomend trying one of their lunch thali options so that all curries can be tasted.
Great food, service and ambience. Would definitely go again.
Mann. This is really one of the best Desi Restaurants in the district. Service can be a little off sometimes, but the food is unbeatable, and the decor/ambiance is awesome.
Tasty dishes. Quantity seems to be less compared to other restaurants

I was pleasantly surprised! My favorite dish to order at an Indian restaurant is chicken tikka masala. The taste was a bit different than I am used to... but it was absolutely delicious! Frankly, this will be my "go to" for Indian food now; it's even tastier than Rasika. The service was great and the ambiance was simple and tasteful; the restaurant was clean and after our appetizers they even gave us new plates and silverware (I hate it when they make us keep our silverware!). I'm a fan!  :-)
Loved the ambience and food. Very authentic food was served forgot to take pictures.

We visited to Washington, and thought of going to indian restaurant and  finally found pappe. Thought the ambience was good. We went in, there are so many vaccant tables, we request them we want particular table, although all the tables are empty they taken time to seat us in that particular table infront of us. Poor hospitality and the server who served us after taking our order, literally we can see he is nodding his head showing some attitude.after waiting for 45 minutes our order arrived and  Food is also not tasty. Prices are very high compared to the prices.

Very bad customer service, we just ordered food and asked how long it’s going to take and he was very rude about it. He rudely walked away from the table shaking his head. They have no knowledge about menu and choice of options that come with. When we asked for the choice of option that comes with the thali he felt very irritated, and not really helpful. We wanted to leave right away but we have already placed the order. Food is also not great, prices are very high compared to quantities. Definitely not a place to go again.
Lamb shank was delicious

We went to Pappe for lunch on a Saturday. Only two tables were occupied. The guy responsible for seating customers was busy on the phone and we were patiently waiting for him to finish... probably waited for a good 5 minutes if not more. Then when he was done talking another group walked in and he greeted them and went ahead to attend to them completely ignoring us. When we pointed out to him that we have been waiting for him, he still decided to attend to the other group first. It felt so insulting to be ignored like this that we just walked out. I am sure that I will never bother to go there again.
Food was tasty however the service can get better.  Staff needs to get trained on handling families with kids.  Ambiance was great.

Overpriced dishes. Food is subpar. Catered to the American crowd. The curry was real runny watered down, as well as the overpriced drinks and cocktails.  I'd stick with Rasika a true jewel in D.C. Pappe is amatuer hour at it's worst. Skip it, you won't miss anything .

I ordered take out at the bar and just got home. The rice that was supposed to come with my entree wasn’t in the bag so I called and asked if they could deliver it. The guy on the phone said I could drive back and pick some up if I wanted to. Not exactly convenient given the parking challenges and the fact it wasn’t my mistake. I asked to at least get some credit back and, after a sign, was transferred to someone I could “talk to about that” - except the phone just rang a few times and then dropped the call. At least the veggie samosa’s I ordered weren’t on the check. Too bad - I was hoping I had found a good neighborhood Indian restaurant.

Excellent food and service. Great ambience too. We enjoyed our meal so much we came back the next day with a larger group, and also referenced it to many other friends in our group, who enjoyed it! Definitely one of the best Indian restaurants I've eaten at.

This is definitely hybrid fusion style Indian food. That being said the attention to detail with the traditional Indian presentation was spot on. Everything we ordered was delicious....try the truffle oil mushroom naan. Wine was good and the best part was its VERY reasonably priced. 6 ppl 300$ family style everyone was happy and full

I went to Pappe the first week they opened and have kept coming back. Their food is incredible. Some of my favorite Indian food in the city. My go to is the Daal Mahkani. It is the best daal I have ever had. They also have a variety of delicious naans. Don't forget to get a mango lassi or one of their delicious desserts as well!
Great ambience. A bit costly. Authentic north indian food. Loved it.

A lovely room and  charming staff at Pappe contribute to a pleasant experience.  A little slow, a little pricey, but really good food .  And LEMONADE!  Don't miss the lemonade.  I have enjoyed 5 dinners there, and especially like the Aleppey fish curry.  I hope they keep up the good work in spite of 14th Street's subtle decline.
Nice place. Nice ambience. Food is decent as well. It's only 4* because it's very difficult to get a table here.
Food is bland. Except for appetizer everything else has just salt and no spices. Its in no way an Indian restaurant. On top of that its costly. Will not recommend if you like spicy food

We got takeout here via caviar. They were fast and relatively inexpensive. The food was excellent and a different style than indian food we are used to having in philadelphia. The dal makhani (sp) was especially delicious! Naan was fresh. The grilled near had a nice dipping sauce with it . Highly recommend this place, though can't speak to eating at the restaurant itself.
Consistently good Indian food on 14th st. Authentic and a great neighborhood spot.

The food is delicious and totally authentic! We had the bhindi and paneer, both of which tasted like home food, and were some of the tastiest dishes I've had in the US. 11/10 would recommend this place!
Disjointed service and the food is overpriced for its quality.
Authentic Indian (Punjabi) food!! Very delicious and great service!
Perfect flavours! Special shout-out to the bhindi jaipuri. Loved everything we ordered.
Excellent food! The laal maas and dal makhni are amazing!
Definitely lives up to the hype. Excellent service! Delicious food.I  think this was as close to authentic North Indian food, I've come across in D.C
Nice India food

Pappe is a uniquely excellent restaurant. Food, service, decor, everything is great. The wait time was a bit long, even with a confirmed reservation, and space is cozy. However, the dining experience makes up for these small inconveniences. The food is probably the best I’ve had outside India. A must visit in DC.
Superb indian food in downtown
Pricey but worth every dollar. Tremendous food. Especially if you're a fan of various fish recipes

Pappe, a case study in why customer service is SO important. If you go to Rose's Luxury or Gravitas, you will be treated like a VIP no matter who you are. The fact that you're a paying customer deems you respect and genuine hospitality. Then there's Pappe. On a Friday afternoon during the tail end of lunch service, my wife and I walked into Pappe. The hostess was on her iPad and it took a minute for her to look up. She looked annoyed we were there and just looked at us forcing us to ask if there was room (obviously, there was room! Literally there were three other people in the room). She acted like we were the biggest inconvenience to enter the restaurant. Okay, everyone has a bad day, so perhaps she just needs the weekend to rest.  We were seated near the window and we waited. Ten minutes passed. Twenty minutes passed. Finally, we approached the hostess asking if a server was assigned our table. She annoyingly walked to the back to check and informed us the server was getting plates for us. We waited. Five minutes. Fifteen minutes. Nothing. My wife then took things into our hands and went back to see where our server was. Five minutes later he came rushing to our table and said, "Are you in a hurry or something?" Maybe he was awkwardly trying to play it off, but in a hurry or not, waiting for 30+ minutes to be acknowledged at a allegedly top restaurant is just rude.  Once we were finally served, we ordered lunch and that did come out pretty fast. My wife ordered the shrimp curry with onion naan. It was decent, but not the best Indian in DC (for that go to Huntington to Dishes of India). I ordered butter chicken, regular naan and mango chutney and I was impressed. It was the best Indian I've had in the city of DC with the exception of the naan (it was just okay). The mango chutney comes in a healthy portion and tastes like red pepper flakes and honey, making it unique and very tasty.  We waited for our bill. Waited some more. I then grabbed the waiter and handed him our card. All in all, the food was good if you order the butter chicken, but for the service, we're unlikely to go back. A three star rating is for the delicious butter chicken, nothing else.

Strategically located on 14th street-probably the only Indian restaurant here. We ordered vegetarian food at our last visit. The tandoori gobi was flavorful, but the portion size was meager (only 4 tiny florets). We ordered a side of the malai kofta and the gravy was luscious, kofta melted in the mouth. Vegetable  korma, missi roti & garlic naan were also well-made. The breads were piping hot and very fresh. The side of rice on the other hand was disappointing- dull white instead of fluffy snow-white grains. It was “jeera rice”, instead of the pulav mentioned on the menu. Overall, there’s room for improvement, but a good start for a new restaurant.

I'm a little surprised by the reviews this place is getting. Maybe we ordered a couple subpar items and it was a bad night, but I was let down by the service, drinks, and dessert.  I should say that the entrees were great. That's most of a person's meal and if you don't stray from that you should be golden.  But the cocktails were too sweet - sometimes cloying. I was very excited for the rum drink with curry leaf. Until I tasted it.  The saffron rice pudding was passable but  none of us could taste the saffron. The carrot cake had something on it that the staff insisted was fruit but that I swear tasted like Parmesan cheese. They comped that when we asked why they'd put Parm all over it (which I appreciate) and brought us a new one with as little of the Parm fruit as possible, but we didn't eat it.  I'm cutting it some slack because they just opened. Hopefully they can work some of the kinks out.

Brand new neighborhood spot (as of early June 2018) that we have been watching them remodel and reading about—we were excited to finally get to try this place. It did not disappoint. Even though we went during the soft opening and they claim to still be working out the kinks, this place was great. The service was very good and staff were kind and knowledgeable. Cocktails were delicious as was the food. We had some standard favorite Indian dishes such as palak paneer, chicken tikki masala, and vindoloo. Everything tasted great. We will absolutely be back, and are thrilled to have a tasty Indian place nearby.

The place looks better than the pics I saw on the eater article, and the staff was warm and friendly. We could not decide which one was better: the food or the decor? Loved the lamb chops, baingan bharta and the authentic vindaloo which packed some heat.

Had a great experience. The hostesses were friendly, and glad to see us and the place  is very chic looking. We loved the Samosas, the shrimp koliwada that we had as appetizers and the palak paneer and sea bass we had as main course with Missi Roti. Great addition to the neighborhood.

TL;DR - Amazing food and drinks, great service and comfortable seating - easily one of the best North Indian fares I've experienced in the US.  Tried the Tandoori Gobi and Paneer Achari Tikka - the marination on the gobi was exquisite and the achar (Indian pickle) on the paneer transported me to a Dhaba in Punjab! The green chilly naan is a must-have for those seeking some of that Indian heat and the Missi Roti is a wonderfully unique addition to the menu. The Malai Kofta came highly recommended and we were not disappointed - people in our group who were not fond of koftas (dumplings) ended the meal craving for more! The drinks were great as well (even a basic mojito tasted brilliant) and the service was incredibly attentive and prompt (our waiter took the time to keep our toddler entertained and ensured we were well taken care of). Extremely chic ambience with comfortable seating and every area of the restaurant was kept sparkling clean. Prices are generally very reasonable for the DC area as well. If you're in the DMV region and love Indian food, Pappe DC should be in your top 3 restaurants to try out!
